results.raw: Man Fatally Shot by Police at 1117 Marquette Ave, Minneapolis, Minnesota, 55403
results.title: Man Fatally Shot by Police

-MuuVhq2JNQbgrYOS7Fg.text: Firefighters are responding to an unconfirmed report of a person shot.

-MuvJEyAQMvNBSr5oqoy.text: According to the Minnesota Department of Public Safety Bureau of Criminal Apprehension, the shooting involved a police officer. It's unclear who fired the shots and if anyone was injured.

nib.text:
An armed man was fatally shot by police who were executing a search warrant in a Downtown West apartment Wednesday morning, officials said.

At 6:48 a.m., MPD SWAT officers responded to the Bolero Flats apartment building at 1117 Marquette Avenue to serve a search warrant related to a homicide investigation being conducted by Saint Paul police. 

In a press briefing Wednesday afternoon, interim Chief Amelia Huffman said the officers loudly announced their presence as they entered the apartment. 

They then encountered a man who was allegedly holding a gun. 

At least one officer fired gunshots, striking him. 

Police and EMS personnel attempted to provide him with first aid before transporting him to an area hospital, where he was pronounced dead. 

A loaded handgun was recovered from the scene. 

The Minnesota Department of Public Safety Bureau of Criminal Apprehension is conducting an investigation.

results.raw: Two Suspects in Custody After Fatal Shooting Outside Education Center at 7450 Penn Ave S, Minneapolis, Minnesota, 55423
results.title: Two Suspects in Custody After Fatal Shooting Outside Education Center

-MuqpADVRQ9umOMMcDYb.text: Incident reported at 7450 Penn Ave S.

-MuqpAE3Dv6pu5oM4Kel.text: Multiple agencies are on scene outside South Education Center.

-Mur0LCnablmse1qR7Fl.text: Police confirmed a shooting took place shortly after noon outside the South Education Center.

nib.text:
Two suspects are in custody following the shooting that left one student dead and two injured outside Richfield’s South Education Center Tuesday.

Police were called to the campus at 7450 Penn Avenue South around 12:07 p.m. 

Arriving officers discovered two students, a 15-year-old boy and a 17-year-old boy, who had been shot on the sidewalk outside of the school.

Both victims were taken to the hospital, where the 15-year-old ​was pronounced deceased. 

The 17-year-old boy was listed in critical condition. 

A 19-year-old also reportedly sustained minor injuries, but it is unclear if they were shot or received further medical treatment.

Nearby schools were placed on lockdown as a precaution. Police searched the area and determined there was no further threat.

On Wednesday, police announced that two suspects, an 18-year-old man and a 19-year-old man, had been arrested. They had not been charged as of Wednesday morning.

In a [press conference](https://minnesota.cbslocal.com/video/6194548-2-teens-arrested-for-shooting-outside-richfield-school/), officials said the shooting occurred during an altercation between the five people outside of the school.

Police stated there is no further threat to the public. 

An investigation is ongoing.
